The paper discusses a novel architecture for managing multimedia applications on 5G systems, which involves the use of SDN and NFV technologies. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving QoE for multimedia services, which suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories. The paper also discusses the limitations of current systems and proposes new features and functionalities, which could place it in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) categories.
